258
00:13:20,282 --> 00:13:22,449
but I guess someone had a secret stash.

259
00:13:22,588 --> 00:13:24,809
I used my allowance and bought some replacements.

260
00:13:24,834 --> 00:13:26,599
Anyway, take a good look at Yukatan.

261
00:13:26,822 --> 00:13:28,182
Notice anything strange?

262
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,766
♪

263
00:13:30,849 --> 00:13:33,116
Well. This may seem pretty obvious.

264
00:13:33,163 --> 00:13:34,729
But she's acting so friendly.

265
00:13:34,822 --> 00:13:38,016
The Kinoshita I know doesn't have
a happy bone in her entire body.

266
00:13:38,099 --> 00:13:40,796
He's right. She's so smiley it's weird.

267
00:13:40,871 --> 00:13:41,716
Bingo!

268
00:13:42,307 --> 00:13:43,974
This is all about her smile.

269
00:13:44,057 --> 00:13:47,519
Think about it for a minute,
the girl hasn't smiled once since she got here.

270
00:13:47,807 --> 00:13:49,766
She didn't crack a smile in her first class.

271
00:13:49,849 --> 00:13:51,932
She didn't so much as smirk
during the whole panties thing,

272
00:13:52,016 --> 00:13:54,157
or during dinner. Or during the king game,

273
00:13:54,182 --> 00:13:56,224
or when she survived the contest with Minori.

274
00:13:56,357 --> 00:13:58,677
Not even when the damn monkey's life was saved.

275
00:13:58,849 --> 00:13:59,412
That's true.

276
00:13:59,459 --> 00:14:02,307
But her happiness here could
just be part of her act, right?

277
00:14:02,387 --> 00:14:03,489
You may be onto something.

278
00:14:03,589 --> 00:14:04,641
But still...

279
00:14:04,724 --> 00:14:06,048
There's a person living with us who is so down

280
00:14:06,099 --> 00:14:08,634
they never smile at all. Don't you think that's sad?

281
00:14:08,682 --> 00:14:10,724
Yeah. Actually, it really is.

282
00:14:10,807 --> 00:14:11,907
I know, right?

283
00:14:12,057 --> 00:14:15,016
If you need smiles. Then have no fear.

284
00:14:15,099 --> 00:14:16,876
The comedy cavalry has arrived!

285
00:14:21,392 --> 00:14:23,726
Fancy running into you here. Kinoshita.

286
00:14:23,751 --> 00:14:27,251
Anyway... How would you feel about
watching me perform a little trick?

287
00:14:33,238 --> 00:14:34,578
Dark matter!

288
00:14:37,349 --> 00:14:38,190
And?

289
00:14:42,263 --> 00:14:44,564
Looks like we're going to have to step it up a notch!

290
00:14:45,682 --> 00:14:46,832
Well, hello!

291
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:53,766
Tickle, tickle, tickle, tickle,
tickle, tickle, tickle...

292
00:14:53,849 --> 00:14:56,682
Minori! Damn you for making me jealous right now!

293
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:58,273
But keep up the good work!

294
00:14:58,353 --> 00:15:00,674
So, tell me. How do you like my technique?

295
00:15:01,099 --> 00:15:02,932
Here, try this on for size.

296
00:15:03,766 --> 00:15:05,766
Okay. How about a little communication?

297
00:15:05,849 --> 00:15:08,585
Talk to me. How else will I know what you like?

298
00:15:09,474 --> 00:15:10,983
I'm... sensitive.

299
00:15:12,644 --> 00:15:15,891
The body doesn't lie. There's no reason to hold back.

300
00:15:15,974 --> 00:15:18,807
Just give yourself over to absolute pleasure!

301
00:15:18,891 --> 00:15:20,974
I give myself, I do!

302
00:15:21,866 --> 00:15:24,941
Come on now. Show me that smile.

303
00:15:26,866 --> 00:15:29,141
Now it's my turn to show you what I've got.

304
00:15:31,185 --> 00:15:32,699
Stop! Don't do this! Please!

305
00:15:32,724 --> 00:15:35,766
I'm drooling!
Seriously, I'm drooling all over the place!

306
00:15:35,849 --> 00:15:37,426
I think I'm going to pee my pants!

307
00:15:47,682 --> 00:15:49,382
You gonna tell me what's going on?

308
00:15:51,690 --> 00:15:54,224
Look. I'm sorry. I really am.

309
00:15:54,307 --> 00:15:56,641
It's just you always seem so glum all the time.

310
00:15:56,724 --> 00:15:59,693
I guess I'm worried life here
isn't really doing it for you.

311
00:16:01,716 --> 00:16:02,572
I see.

312
00:16:03,266 --> 00:16:05,573
So this whole thing was about getting me to smile?

313
00:16:05,653 --> 00:16:06,849
Dumb. I know.

314
00:16:06,932 --> 00:16:09,392
We didn't mean any harm by it, I swear. But...

315
00:16:09,891 --> 00:16:12,182
We did get a little carried away, didn't we?

316
00:16:12,266 --> 00:16:13,641
I can't smile.

317
00:16:13,724 --> 00:16:14,328
Huh?

318
00:16:15,557 --> 00:16:18,323
I try. But it doesn't work.

319
00:16:24,178 --> 00:16:29,208
At first, they said my expression seemed
a little stiff and that I needed to relax.

320
00:16:29,557 --> 00:16:31,390
But I really didn't think much of it.

321
00:16:31,769 --> 00:16:33,409
I figured I was just tired.

322
00:16:36,724 --> 00:16:40,512
But. Over time,
I completely lost the ability to smile.

323
00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:43,684
Eventually, I couldn't summon
up other expressions either.

324
00:16:43,984 --> 00:16:47,378
The way things were, it didn't make
sense for me to stay where I was.

325
00:16:47,585 --> 00:16:49,474
So I left, just like that monkey.

326
00:16:49,557 --> 00:16:50,904
Yeah... But...

327
00:16:51,060 --> 00:16:53,665
In the end, the monkey found a
safe place where he belonged.

328
00:16:53,724 --> 00:16:55,258
So you can too...

329
00:16:55,836 --> 00:16:57,264
That's nice. Thanks.

330
00:17:00,113 --> 00:17:01,459
But there's no point.

331
00:17:11,016 --> 00:17:12,891
How can someone not be able to smile?

332
00:17:12,974 --> 00:17:14,474
It just doesn't make any sense.

333
00:17:14,557 --> 00:17:16,109
I'm guessing it's psychological.

334
00:17:16,349 --> 00:17:18,738
That's the only explanation I can come up with.

335
00:17:20,099 --> 00:17:21,933
Maybe it was all too much for her.

336
00:17:22,516 --> 00:17:24,782
Maybe she got burnt out living in the limelight

337
00:17:24,807 --> 00:17:27,738
and always trying to meet other people's expectations.

338
00:17:28,266 --> 00:17:29,281
She needs rest.

339
00:17:29,306 --> 00:17:31,157
That'll make her go back to normal, won't it?

340
00:17:31,182 --> 00:17:33,182
Well. One can always hope.

341
00:17:33,266 --> 00:17:35,104
I want her to smile again.

342
00:17:35,974 --> 00:17:38,212
Do you think it's selfish of me to want that for her?

343
00:17:38,292 --> 00:17:39,916
If it is, maybe I don't care.

344
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:54,714
Kousaku. Kousaku!

345
00:17:58,016 --> 00:17:59,399
Whoa! Who are you?

346
00:17:59,557 --> 00:18:02,641
Do you not recognize me? Silly.

347
00:18:02,724 --> 00:18:04,156
I am Gaia.

348
00:18:04,641 --> 00:18:05,855
Gaia?

349
00:18:06,516 --> 00:18:09,803
Yes. I have come to deliver a message.

350
00:18:10,093 --> 00:18:11,651
Uh... What message?

351
00:18:12,974 --> 00:18:14,641
You must remember, Kousaku.

352
00:18:14,724 --> 00:18:17,016
Remember what mankind has done to me.

353
00:18:17,099 --> 00:18:18,974
Remember your ties to the soil.

354
00:18:19,057 --> 00:18:23,363
Please. Whatever the future holds. Stand firm.

355
00:18:24,938 --> 00:18:26,896
Gaia is always with you, my friend.

356
00:18:27,193 --> 00:18:30,409
Till the end of time. Listen and you will hear me.

357
00:18:30,496 --> 00:18:32,391
Imploring you to honor the land!

358
00:18:32,474 --> 00:18:33,682
No. Don't leave me here!

359
00:18:33,766 --> 00:18:35,599
Please! Gaia!

360
00:18:35,682 --> 00:18:38,266
Gaia!

361
00:18:46,766 --> 00:18:49,074
What was all that? Wacky.

362
00:18:52,724 --> 00:18:55,485
"Remember what mankind has done to me."

363
00:19:12,108 --> 00:19:15,516
Guys. I think I'm going to take Ringo to you-know-where.

364
00:19:16,849 --> 00:19:18,831
I really want to show her that soil.

365
00:19:19,224 --> 00:19:22,699
Good idea. After all, she does have
something in common with it right now.

366
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:24,007
Yeah. That's true.

367
00:19:24,032 --> 00:19:28,453
Maybe seeing that field and hearing a positive
message would help her realize there is always hope.

368
00:19:33,614 --> 00:19:37,932
Schools like ours have things called
"Agricultural Clubs", or "Ag Clubs" for short!

369
00:19:38,075 --> 00:19:40,991
Well, at any rate, we're headed to the site of a project

370
00:19:41,016 --> 00:19:43,102
we inherited from some former students.

371
00:19:43,174 --> 00:19:44,008
A project?

372
00:19:44,175 --> 00:19:44,861
Yes.

373
00:19:44,928 --> 00:19:47,328
And if you're willing, we'd like for you to join in!

374
00:19:54,682 --> 00:19:55,599
This is it?

375
00:19:55,682 --> 00:19:56,222
Yep!

376
00:19:56,558 --> 00:19:58,266
Not the tomato field over there?

377
00:19:58,557 --> 00:19:59,941
Nope. Here first.

378
00:20:03,390 --> 00:20:04,719
Try touching the soil.

379
00:20:04,991 --> 00:20:05,616
Right now?

380
00:20:05,647 --> 00:20:06,146
Yeah.

381
00:20:14,932 --> 00:20:16,641
It feels hard and dry.

382
00:20:16,724 --> 00:20:18,199
Mm-hmm.

383
00:20:18,224 --> 00:20:19,740
The reason it feels that way is 'cause the soil is dead.

384
00:20:19,991 --> 00:20:20,973
It's dead?

385
00:20:21,516 --> 00:20:22,994
It's a figure of speech.

386
00:20:23,238 --> 00:20:25,700
Crops won't grow here in its current condition.

387
00:20:26,266 --> 00:20:27,488
That's so sad...

388
00:20:27,825 --> 00:20:29,159
It's replant failure.

389
00:20:29,391 --> 00:20:31,074
Remember, Miss Becky talked about it?

390
00:20:32,391 --> 00:20:35,099
If you continue to grow the same plant in the same soil

391
00:20:35,182 --> 00:20:37,849
over and over, eventually, it won't grow anymore.

392
00:20:37,932 --> 00:20:40,766
Yes. That's exactly right.

393
00:20:41,641 --> 00:20:43,270
People try to get around this problem.

394
00:20:43,557 --> 00:20:46,618
They use chemical fertilizers
to try to stimulate new growth.

395
00:20:47,027 --> 00:20:50,355
But that only leads to disease and
winds up damaging the environment.

396
00:20:51,182 --> 00:20:53,752
What you're seeing is the result of a vicious cycle.

397
00:20:58,463 --> 00:21:02,307
Will the soil ever go back to
normal again or is it dead forever?

398
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:08,631
The process takes time.

399
00:21:08,766 --> 00:21:11,495
This field started out with that very same soil.

400
00:21:11,932 --> 00:21:13,865
It's been there since the very beginning.

401
00:21:14,932 --> 00:21:16,849
Previous Ag Clubbers started this project

402
00:21:16,932 --> 00:21:18,082
and we inherited it.

403
00:21:18,391 --> 00:21:21,581
They worked for seven years. Day in and day out.

404
00:21:21,891 --> 00:21:23,089
Now it's our turn.

405
00:21:24,057 --> 00:21:25,411
Seven years?

406
00:21:25,849 --> 00:21:26,879
It's not fixed.

407
00:21:26,904 --> 00:21:29,525
There's still a lot to do to
get this soil back to normal.

408
00:21:30,571 --> 00:21:32,641
But even though this soil has a long way to go,

409
00:21:32,724 --> 00:21:34,349
this field is slowly improving,

410
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:37,092
doing her best to live on the land she's got.

411
00:21:40,741 --> 00:21:44,075
So, eventually, this place will be reborn?

412
00:22:18,239 --> 00:22:20,426
Hey, those tomatoes look good.

413
00:22:20,615 --> 00:22:21,324
Can I eat one?

414
00:22:21,349 --> 00:22:22,474
What? Now?

415
00:22:23,186 --> 00:22:24,102
I'd like to.

416
00:22:24,141 --> 00:22:25,420
Sure. Why not?

417
00:22:30,474 --> 00:22:31,074
Here.

418
00:22:41,773 --> 00:22:42,659
It's bitter.

419
00:22:42,752 --> 00:22:44,783
Yeah, that's 'cause it's not ripe just yet.

420
00:22:45,016 --> 00:22:46,682
Still, I'll eat it.

421
00:22:46,766 --> 00:22:47,520
Huh?

422
00:22:50,345 --> 00:22:52,298
Yep, definitely bitter.

423
00:22:52,563 --> 00:22:53,372
Told you.

424
00:22:53,877 --> 00:22:54,787
Yeah, but...

425
00:22:56,704 --> 00:22:57,844
I like it.

426
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,029
Whoa. You... !

427
00:23:03,436 --> 00:23:04,170
What?

428
00:23:04,656 --> 00:23:06,263
Wait, this one's more ripe! Here.

429
00:23:06,288 --> 00:23:07,980
It'll taste way better!

430
00:23:08,432 --> 00:23:10,107
Mine is even riper than hers!

431
00:23:10,349 --> 00:23:11,823
No, no, no, stick with mine.

432
00:23:11,848 --> 00:23:14,065
It's definitely juicier than Kei's! Take it!

433
00:23:14,307 --> 00:23:15,354
Mine is fresher!

434
00:23:15,607 --> 00:23:16,952
Food made with love,

435
00:23:16,977 --> 00:23:19,939
love of the earth, love of people, spreads happiness.

436
00:23:20,224 --> 00:23:21,032
The secret?

437
00:23:21,391 --> 00:23:23,723
Reminding yourself that it's Nature's gift.

438
00:23:24,141 --> 00:23:27,393
Working the land is one the
greatest joys life has to offer.

439
00:23:27,865 --> 00:23:28,834
One day, I hope...

440
00:23:29,349 --> 00:23:32,151
I hope you'll experience that joy firsthand.

441
00:23:36,630 --> 00:23:38,936
Farming's Five Top Four!

